Python library for analyzing Go binaries PyGoRE is a simple to use Python library for analyzing Go binaries compiled with Go compiler. How to use Use pip install pygore to download and install the library. Import it into your project. Write a new cool tool. Sample code import pygore testfile = '/path/to/go/binary/file' f = pygore.GoFile(testfile) c = f.get_compiler_version() print('Compiler: {}
Timestamp: {}
SHA {}
'. format(c.name, c.timestamp, c.sha)) pkgs = f.
